*lame edit*<br>
Here's another analogy.  At Burger King you can &quot;have it your way,&quot; right?  Even though you can get it any way you like it (the equivalent of not reading a post that doesn't interest you) they don't change the menu to include the item the way you ordered it do they?(the equivalent of making extra categories)<br>
<br>
food for thought (pun intended)<br>
