<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:verdana;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.xevnull.com" target="top">&lt;NuLL&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elrynia>elrynia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnomish Pr0n Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1068<br> <font color=#330000>(12/9/03 6:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help provide a boost to the rants forum</span><hr size=1> I don't have a huge opinion one way or the other anymore.  <br>
<br>
I don't think we need a political rant forum.  Keeping rants together in one forum is better for traffic (not that we have traffic goals or anything)  It is easier for mods to keep track of fewer forums.  And it would eliminate all the *please move this thread* posts.  Some posts don't start political, but they end up political so then we have all these people bitching to get things moved, so thats another headache.  Plus, political rants does not get the traffic regular rants does, so if you start this great thread and it goes political on you, it will have to be moved which can pretty much kill the thread.<br>
<br>
None of this is really that huge of a deal, it's just forum sections.<br>
I just don't see the point in sectioning them off in the first place.  I thought the argument was because people don't want to read the political rants.  So?  I don't want to read posts by Crylin or posts about peoples cars, does that mean they should get their own forum?  I think we make things far too complicated.  If you don't want to read political rants, skip over them.  Just because a rant is in the rant section, it does not obligate one to read it and the political nature of many threads is hardly hidden.<br>
<br>
If we want a better functioning forum I think it should be pruned. I think we can do away with polls and rant polls, hardly anyone goes there.  Keep regular polls in general, rant polls in rants and have mods close them every week or so if they clutter stuff up.  I think we could lose uber or at least combine uber and tactics.  Shrink the guild forums into a sticky of guilds in general.  People looking for guild could ask in general.   Raiding is hardly ever used and there is nothing there that could not go in general.  We could sticky a list of tradeskillers in general and lose tradeskills.  Not a popular forum and could easily be posted in general.  I'd keep /ooc.<br>
<br>
So here is the forum line up I think we could work easily with.<br>
<br>
General<br>
Market Place<br>
Ask the Mods<br>
Rants<br>
Uber<br>
/ooc<br>
Archive<br>
Quests (this is a maybe, another low traffic forum)<br>
<br>
I think this set up would promote more traffic in under used sections and be alot easier for mods to keep track of.<br>
<br>
